element.name: Sidetracked - Malahide by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

p.b: Malahide railway station is located on the main Dublin-Belfast railway line.

long-description.p:
The station opened 1844. The present station was built entirely by Great Northern Railway, they constructed a typical yellow brick station building as well as the footbridge and signal cabin.
There's also the typical GNR stations masters’ house adjacent to the station. All of these are well maintained, and the station building retains its GNR canopy.
In 2000 Malahide became the second northern terminus of the DART service.
Side-Tracked Caches are intended to provide quick Cache-and-dashes at Train Stations.
The Cache is a small micro container please rehide it well to prevent the many muggles from discovering it.
